    <div class="container">
           <h1>COMPUTER Troubleshooting & Maintenance Services</h1>
        <p>
            A comprehensive list of computer troubleshooting and maintenance services typically includes both proactive and reactive measures. These services can be performed by an individual or a professional and cover a wide range of hardware, software, and networking issues.
        </p>

        <h2>Common Troubleshooting and Repair Services</h2>
        <p>
            These services address specific problems that have already occurred.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Diagnostic Services:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Hardware Diagnostics:</strong> Identifying failing or faulty hardware components (e.g., hard drive, RAM, motherboard, power supply).</li>
                    <li><strong>Software Diagnostics:</strong> Pinpointing the cause of software crashes, slow performance, or system errors.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Virus and Malware Removal:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Deep scanning and removal of viruses, spyware, ransomware, and other malicious software.</li>
                    <li>Installing and configuring antivirus and anti-malware software for future protection.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Performance Optimization:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>System Tune-up:</strong> Cleaning up temporary files, clearing browser caches, and removing unnecessary programs.</li>
                    <li><strong>Startup Program Management:</strong> Disabling non-essential applications that launch at boot to improve startup speed.</li>
                    <li><strong>Disk Defragmentation:</strong> Rearranging fragmented data on a hard disk drive (HDD) for faster access. This is not necessary for Solid State Drives (SSDs).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Operating System (OS) and Software Repair:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Troubleshooting and resolving OS issues, including boot failures and the "Blue Screen of Death" (BSOD).</li>
                    <li>Repairing or reinstalling corrupted operating systems.</li>
                    <li>Troubleshooting and resolving issues with specific applications.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Hardware Repair and Replacement:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Component Replacement:</strong> Installing new or upgraded components like RAM, hard drives (HDD or SSD), graphics cards (GPU), or power supplies (PSU).</li>
                    <li><strong>Laptop Repair:</strong> Fixing broken laptop screens, keyboards, or charging ports.</li>
                    <li><strong>Overheating Issues:</strong> Cleaning out dust from fans and internal components, and ensuring proper airflow.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Data Services:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Data Recovery:</strong> Attempting to retrieve lost or corrupted data from a failed hard drive or storage device.</li>
                    <li><strong>Data Backup and Transfer:</strong> Setting up a reliable backup system and securely transferring data from an old computer to a new one.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Network and Connectivity Troubleshooting:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Diagnosing and fixing issues with Wi-Fi, Ethernet, and internet connections.</li>
                    <li>Setting up and securing local area networks (LANs).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Regular Maintenance Services</h2>
        <p>
            These are proactive services designed to prevent problems before they happen.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <strong>Software Updates and Patching:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ensuring the operating system, drivers, and applications are up-to-date with the latest security patches and performance enhancements.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Physical Cleaning:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Dust removal from the computer's interior, fans, and vents to prevent overheating and component damage.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Security Audits:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Checking firewall settings, password strength, and overall system security.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Backup Solutions:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Implementing and verifying regular data backups, either to an external drive or a cloud service.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>General Health Checks:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Conducting routine diagnostic scans to monitor the health of the hardware and software.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Computer Setup:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>Setting up new computers, including hardware installation, software configuration, and data transfer.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
